  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Unwilling to change their opinions&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I have been unfortunate enough to need this service over the past few years, as I am young I have been constantly told that it is unlikely that I would have any real gynaecological issues, and it has been like pulling teeth trying to convince the consultant to perform any tests. Was offered an ultrasound only and afterwards doctors repeatedly attempted to discharge me without doing any further tests, including a smear. Have had to ask repeatedly for more tests to be done, some of which I was told (incorrectly) that the department doesn't do, including blood tests to check hormone levels  (despite signs on the walls to show which hormone blood tests should be done). Ended up having these done with my GP, who told me the actual results, when reported to gynaecology I was repeatedly told that the results of these and other tests were 'normal'. Repeatedly told by my Dr what they would choose to do if they had my problem, with refusal to understand my fears associated with certain treatments. Additionally, talked to my (male) partner as if he was the patient and as if his opinion on my treatment was more important than mine, tried to encourage my partner to agree with them on what my treatment should be. I contacted PALS who were also of no help and uninterested in hearing my side of the communications. If you have these issues don't bother persisting like I did, go to a different hospital instead of wasting months trying to convince your doctor to care.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
